HEADWORD: Blastostyle
<hw>Blas"to*style</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>blasto`s</grk> sprout, bud + <ets><?/</ets> a pillar.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>In certain hydroids, an imperfect zooid, whose
special function is to produce medusoid buds. See <er>Hydroidea</er>,
and <er>Athecata</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blast pipe</ent>⟦br⟧
